	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p>Collections on a&#47;c Occident<lb/> from <persName>I. Cohen</persName> 900<lb/> rep comp <hi rend="underline">180</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">&#36;7.20</hi></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#44; I hand you<lb/> enclosed my check on Mechanic<lb/> Bank <placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; for<lb/> Seven 20&#47; Dolls proceeds 50<lb/> collections from <persName>Jacob<lb/> Cohen Esqr.</persName>  I remit this small<lb/> amount because I think<lb/> every dollar you can re&#45;<lb/>&#61;ceive at present you<lb/> can find use for in your<lb/> <sic>enterprize</sic>.  I regretted much<lb/> in finding you absent from <placeName>Phil<hi rend="sup">a</hi></placeName> on my sojourn there<lb/> I hope your printer &#38; stereo<lb/>&#45;type are progressing rapidly<lb/> to a conclusion&#44; as the<lb/> people are very anx</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>&#61;ious to see the Bible&#8212;<lb/>  What is the meaning<lb/> of <persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi>. Wise</persName> being called<lb/> to the City of <placeName><sic>Cincinatti</sic></placeName><lb/> to take charge of what was<lb/> hitherto considered an<lb/> orthodox congregation<lb/> are the people so indif<lb/>&#61;ferent or changeable in their<lb/> opinions or has <persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> W.</persName> be<lb/> come more orthodox<lb/> in his outward expressi<lb/>&#61;ons &#38; conduct.  At least<lb/> his <sic>prevale</sic> opinions are<lb/> I am sure not undergone<lb/> a change for <persName>Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi> Mr Meyer</persName><lb/> rec<hi rend="sup">d</hi> a letter from him&#44; ad<lb/>&#61;vising of his call &#38; so treats<lb/> it as a triumph of Reform<lb/> &#38; boats<add>&#63;</add> that in less than<lb/> 10 years the whole of the<lb/> Jews in the<lb/> <placeName>United States</placeName> will be come<lb/> reformers&#44; so that I am</p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p>of opinion that the Dr<lb/> is an hypocrite&#44; his writings<lb/> lately certainly has a differ<lb/>&#45;ent colouring to what his<lb/> precious opinions were<lb/> &#38; his essays in your jour<lb/>&#61;nal certainly indicate a very<lb/> great modification at least<lb/> of his former negative ideas<lb/> of Messiah &#38; resurrection<lb/>&#8212;do please enlighten me<lb/> early&#8212;in regard to the<lb/> D<hi rend="sup">r</hi>.&#39;s call.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please advise me how<lb/> much <persName>Oppenheim</persName> owes for<lb/> the Occident as well as <persName>Myers</persName><lb/> are they all desirous to pay<lb/> <persName>Michl Lazarus</persName> has not paid<lb/> me for a long while&#44; does he still<lb/> take the O.&#63;  Are there any other<lb/> dues to you <sic>here&#44;</sic>&#63;</p>
				<p>Are we to have any of <persName>Peixotto</persName><lb/> <add>&#63;</add>&#63;  Hoping you<lb/> are well&#44; in which all your<lb/> friends here unite.  I remain<lb/> your friend</p>
				<p><persName role="author">Samuel Hart Senr.</persName></p>
				<p><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>Nov 16 1853</date></p>
